content.description: Nice little finger crack with lots of feet that help the marginal finger placements.
content.protection: Standard rack, small finger-sized cams mostly
content.location: Around the arete to the left. Uphill on the walk off ramp before you hit "Matt's tiny crack".

content.description: Face climb with lots of jugs that is easily protected with 2-3 cams in hand-sized crack.
content.protection: Standard rack, but you will only use like 2-3 cams. #1 and #2.
content.location: Up hill on the walk-off hill to the left of the arete.  Main crack about halfway up ramp.  Just left of "twitter fingers".

content.description: Main climb on this wall.  This is the small hand/finger crack just right of the arete.  Starts out with foot jam in crack and plenty of hands, including under cling in horizontal crack.  Moves up on a ledge where you have to traverse over to flared crack with plenty of face holds that you follow to top.
content.protection: Standard rack, #1 and under. Bring the small stuff.
content.location: crack just right of the main arete on "Not Worth It" Just left of bush that starts "Enchie, Minnie, off-width.

content.description: This is an off-width start to "Enchi, Minnie, Oye".  Off width crack until you get to the area you traverse to flared crack to finish.
content.protection: Bigger cams for off-width section, but then small stuff for flared crack.
content.location: Just right of "Enchi, Minnie, Oye" starts over a bush.

pathTokens: Laramie Peak Wildlife Habitat Management Area
